# Exact repo-relative paths exempt from scripts/check-typography.ts
# (one per line; exact match, never a prefix).
#
# EMPTY, and it should stay that way: every file in the repo - including the
# zh locale bundles and translated docs - uses ASCII punctuation for
# everything the checker bans (the CJK marks it always allows in CJK-context
# files remain in use). Add a path only with an explicit, reviewed decision.
#
# Whole-script CJK containment (an untranslated Chinese label leaking into an
# English surface) is policed separately by scripts/check-cjk.ts, not here.
# Non-banned functional glyphs (U+2022 masking bullet, U+2192, U+26A0, U+2260)
# are not look-alikes and need no exemption.
#
# Known gap, accepted for now: release-please's generated CHANGELOG.md quotes
# two pre-policy commit subjects containing U+2014, so the release PR's
# typography check fails until a changelog sanitizer lands in
# Vivswan/repo-platform. After merging a release, ASCII-ify the frozen lines
# on main to keep main green.
